OL,7,FIt came as support for devolution had
OL,8,Fgrown during the 1980s and 1990s.
OL,10,FThe Labour party, led by Tony Blair,
OL,11,Fwent on to make Welsh and Scottish
OL,12,Freferendums a manifesto commitment
OL,13,Fduring the 1997 general election
OL,14,Fcampaign, which it won by a landslide.
OL,16,FThe first elections to the Senedd `
OL,17,Fthen called the Welsh Assembly ` were
OL,18,Fheld on 6 May 1999, with its first
OL,19,Fmeeting a few days later on 12 May.
