OL,4,C25 years since the first Senedd
OL,5,Celection
OL,7,FThat essentially means the UK
OL,8,FGovernment maintains power over
OL,9,Fcertain areas, such as defence, while
OL,10,Fthe rest are put in the hands of Welsh
OL,11,Fpoliticians.
OL,13,FIn another significant development, in
OL,14,F2020 the National Assembly was
OL,15,Fofficially named the Senedd Cymru or
OL,16,FWelsh Parliament, reflecting its law-
OL,17,Fmaking and tax-setting powers.
OL,19,FThe same year also saw 16 and 17-year-
OL,20,Folds given a vote in Senedd elections
OL,21,F` next set to be held in 2026.
